BT /F2 20 Tf 54 740 Td (AI-Powered RAG System for Cybercrime) Tj ET
BT /F2 20 Tf 54 713 Td (Investigation) Tj ET
BT /F2 15 Tf 54 662 Td (1. Executive Summary) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 628 Td (This project implements a case-agnostic Retrieval-Augmented Generation \(RAG\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 615 Td (system to help detectives investigate cybercrime case files. The system ingests) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 602 Td (case documents, stores them as vector embeddings, retrieves the most relevant) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 589 Td (evidence for a detective's natural-language question, and generates a grounded) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 576 Td (investigation report with source citations.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 555 Td (The key design goal is not to make the LLM "solve the case" from memory. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 542 Td (LLM is used as an assistant that reasons only over retrieved evidence. This) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 529 Td (keeps the system reusable for future cases and reduces hallucination risk.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 508 Td (The final system supports:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 487 Td (- Loading all case files from a generic data/ directory.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 472 Td (- Converting documents into embeddings.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 457 Td (- Persisting embeddings in ChromaDB.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 442 Td (- Multi-step retrieval with query expansion and relevance grading.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 427 Td (- Ranked evidence with confidence scores.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 412 Td (- Investigation reports grounded in cited evidence.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 397 Td (- Evaluation for retrieval quality, citation validity, and adversarial prompt) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 382 Td (  injection behavior.) Tj ET
BT /F2 15 Tf 54 351 Td (2. Problem and Requirements) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 317 Td (The scenario is a crypto exchange hack where investigators collected eight case) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 304 Td (files. Some files contain useful evidence, while others are irrelevant or) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 291 Td (misleading. The system must help a detective ask questions and identify the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 278 Td (most relevant evidence.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 257 Td (The requirements are:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 236 Td (- Load all eight case files.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 221 Td (- Convert each case file into vector embeddings.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 206 Td (- Choose and justify a retrieval strategy.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 191 Td (- Retrieve the most relevant documents for a detective question.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 176 Td (- Rank results and show confidence scores.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 161 Td (- Explain why documents were selected.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 146 Td (- Generate a detailed investigation report using an LLM.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 131 Td (- Keep prompts case-agnostic so the same system can support future cases.) Tj ET
BT /F2 15 Tf 54 98 Td (3. High-Level Architecture) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 526 28 Td (Page 1) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
