BT /F2 15 Tf 54 740 Td (6. Vector Database Choice) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 706 Td (The project uses ChromaDB as the vector database.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 685 Td (Reasons:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 664 Td (- Simple local setup.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 649 Td (- Persistent storage.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 634 Td (- Supports cosine similarity.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 619 Td (- Stores vectors, document text, and metadata together.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 604 Td (- Good fit for a small case-file corpus and a take-home project.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 581 Td (Confidence scores are derived from ChromaDB cosine distance:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 560 Td (confidence = 1 - cosine_distance) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 539 Td (Production note:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 518 Td (ChromaDB is appropriate for this scope. In a larger production environment, I) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 505 Td (would consider pgvector, Pinecone, Weaviate, or a managed vector store depending) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 492 Td (on requirements such as scale, multi-user access, audit logging, access control,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 479 Td (and operations.) Tj ET
BT /F2 15 Tf 54 448 Td (7. Retrieval Strategy) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 414 Td (The system uses multi-step retrieval instead of single-step retrieval.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 393 Td (The pipeline is:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 372 Td (1. Expand the detective's question into focused sub-queries.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 357 Td (2. Search the vector database with the original query and each sub-query.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 342 Td (3. Merge and deduplicate candidate documents.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 327 Td (4. Keep the maximum cosine similarity as each document's confidence score.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 312 Td (5. Use an LLM relevance grader to judge candidates against the original) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 297 Td (   question.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 284 Td (6. Return relevant documents as evidence and show excluded documents with) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 269 Td (   reasons.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 238 Td (Why Multi-Step Retrieval?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 208 Td (Single-step nearest-neighbor retrieval is simpler, but it has two major) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 195 Td (weaknesses for this scenario.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 174 Td (First, investigation questions often require multiple documents. For example,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 161 Td ("How were the stolen funds laundered?" may require one document about the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 148 Td (initial wallet movement and another document about the mixer. A single nearest) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 135 Td (document cannot fully answer that.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 114 Td (Second, the corpus contains red herrings. Irrelevant files can share terms like) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 101 Td ("breach," "server," "malware," or "attack." A basic vector search can retrieve) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 88 Td (these because of surface-level similarity.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 526 28 Td (Page 4) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
